Situated in river north, this place offers creative bites in a warm, cozy atmosphere with attentive, welcoming service. We had a good time dining in. Potions are small so approach the menu as a tasting-style one. Tako Taco (the Octopus Taco) is an appetizing specialty that you shouldn’t miss. Nigiris didn’t live up to our expectations, we got the Ikura & Uni, Unagi, and Zuke Salmon 🍣 All fish does taste fresh but some dishes were served a bit cold (cold rice on rolls) that took a bit away from the overall experience.

I'm usually pretty picky when it comes to sushi. A lot of places deemed good I just don't like. I'm picky. And I don't usually write reviews. Sushi-san is amazing. Like I wasn't sure about it at first, because my sister doesn't eat sushi like I do so she and I was put off a little by no ramen. But it caused her to pick something else and that was the lettuce wrap. The beef was so tender it was amazing! I got the sushi myself. Now, the pricing is a bit up there. Not like super pricey but expect to pay at least 100 if you with 1 other person and want to indulge in more than 1 roll. They have different versions of the tuna and the bluefin was mouth melting. I got the bluefin tuna and avacado. 10pc. It was $20 we'll worth the money. I got the spices salmon also. That was 18 for 5 pieces. That was very good also. Like, it was all so good! The amberjack nigri was just so amazing in it's taste also! I was craving more and more but money is not something that I have a lot of, not my sister. The staff was laid back and nice! They got us what we needed. We did have to remind once for a item my sister wanted with her chicken tenders but that's not a big deal. This place was amazing. and I don't say that lightly. If you love sushi, this is a must try spot! The 20 dollar 2pc nigri I'm sure would be well worth the 20 dollars also!!

Insanely fresh fish, great service and your not-so-typical sushi place atmosphere. This place rocks.  Came here without reservations on a Thursday night around 9. I was worried because it was insanely packed and we didn't make a reservation. However, we got seated within 20 minutes so it wasn't too bad.  I loved the vibes here right off the bat. Lively music, modern & fun decor. Not your typical "quiet and calm" sushi theme.  First we ordered some miso soup, loved the presentation. Had great flavor as well. Then we ordered the nigiri 8 pcs set, Mr. Maguro set, ginger salmon roll, spicy tuna roll, crunchy avocado roll & the Thai basil chicken rice.  Breakdown-  -Nigiri 8 pcs set: delicious. Perfect ratio of sashimi to rice & the fish was so fresh and smooth it melted in your mouth like butter. This is a must. -Maguro set: absolutely amazing. Great variety, the tuna pieces in this are to die for. -Ginger salmon: very unique flavor, fresh & spicy with the ginger kick -Spicy tuna: again, like butter. Nailing the basic rolls is important. -Crunchy avocado: Decent but wouldn't get it again. It's so creamy the texture of the roll ends up tasting mushy. -Thai basil chicken rice: Incredible flavor and heat.  It's hard to find a sushi place in the city that doesn't take a major toll on your bank account. But here you get the upmost quality at a very reasonable price. Definitely a fan & can't wait to come back.

Great service and accomodating staff make this restaurant a desirable venue. However, the tendency to stick to a pre-set menu, supposedly done for ease of ordering, or to a rather limited cutomisable menu, makes it challenging to order food if one happen to dislike one of the included foods. The kitchen is willing to make substitutions and custom orders, however the fact that this is a necessity in the first place makes ordering an inconvenient experience. When it comes to the menu of individual items, the options tend to have complex flavour profiles, such as combining squid and matcha into one item, making it hard to order anything simple if one is just there for rhe sushi. There are also not very many a la carte sushi options priced at 10 dollars or below. The desserts, however, are fantastic, such as the "Japanese Pancakes", which come with a delicious brown sugar syrup. If you are looking for a new and unique experience for the palate however, Sushi-san is for you.

Game Over!  Best sushi in Chicago.  The environment is outstanding, too.  We had to eat here twice while we were in town.  Please open one in Charlotte!!!
